WEBVTT

00:00.962 --> 00:03.424
Our next reading this morning is going to come from the book of Hebrews.

00:03.965 --> 00:09.410
We're reading Hebrews chapter 10, verses 19 through 25.

00:13.594 --> 00:16.917
Hebrews chapter 10, verses 19 through 25.

00:20.520 --> 00:30.610
Therefore, my friends, since we have confidence to enter the sanctuary by the blood of Jesus, by the new and living way that he opened for us through the curtain, that is through his flesh,

00:30.978 --> 00:45.358
And since we have a great priest over the house of God, let us approach with a true heart and full assurance of faith with our heart sprinkled clean from an evil conscience and our bodies washed with pure water.

00:45.799 --> 00:51.747
Let us hold fast the confession of our hope without wavering for he who has promised is faithful.

00:52.448 --> 00:59.698
And let us consider how to provoke one another to love and good deeds, not neglecting to meet together as is the habit of sun.

00:59.938 --> 01:04.484
but encouraging one another all the more as you see the day approaching.

01:05.025 --> 01:06.387
This is the word of God for the people of God.

01:06.948 --> 01:07.869
Thanks be to God.

01:10.252 --> 01:14.418
One of the perks for working for the church is I get to come to the church anytime I want to.

01:16.060 --> 01:21.788
In fact, many a day, though many of you, I've had phone calls with some of you all that are long and winding.

01:21.828 --> 01:25.173
And so when I'm on the phone with somebody, I don't sit still in my office.

01:25.213 --> 01:26.034
I have to move.

01:26.402 --> 01:33.931
So there's been some days when I've been on the phone with somebody and I'll find myself walking through the sanctuary just over and over again.

01:34.232 --> 01:38.537
Some days on particularly stressful days or stressful phone calls, I just walk that way.

01:38.877 --> 01:41.040
There's been a couple of times, you know we have a creek back there?

01:42.442 --> 01:43.863
I've wound up at the creek a couple of times.

01:44.184 --> 01:46.587
So, you know, I like to walk and talk.

01:46.647 --> 01:47.668
I like to walk and talk.

01:47.988 --> 01:55.858
But I love being able to just come into the sanctuary when the owner particularly

01:56.898 --> 01:57.378
Pretty day.

01:59.020 --> 02:00.622
Sometimes the light will come through that sting.

02:00.642 --> 02:01.803
Let's win it right there just perfectly.

02:03.444 --> 02:04.025
Just perfectly.

02:04.806 --> 02:10.251
You know, it'll kind of start falling around here and just kind of working its way back towards the back.

02:11.132 --> 02:19.820
Our, some of y'all know this, but Heart Hall, where we have Wizard out Live Mills, that was our first sanctuary before we built this building in 99.

02:20.701 --> 02:25.906
And on certain days, when the sun's setting just right,

02:27.010 --> 02:35.458
it'll come through that window back there and come through that red cross in just a stunningly beautiful fashion.

02:36.959 --> 02:43.706
That's why we're talking in the bulletin about all the stuff of the colors because there's something beautiful.

02:44.867 --> 02:50.432
As Meg said, we are gifted and on a rainy day like today, I know a lot of folks are watching online and I'm glad for that.

02:51.032 --> 02:56.978
But there is something beautiful about being in this place, being in

02:57.474 --> 02:57.814
Church.

02:59.737 --> 03:00.839
But church is interesting.

03:00.879 --> 03:04.243
I don't know if y'all know this, but our church has a South Campus.

03:04.343 --> 03:04.824
Did y'all know that?

03:04.884 --> 03:06.526
And not our South building over there.

03:07.267 --> 03:08.589
We're talking about a South Campus.

03:08.770 --> 03:14.317
It's a, it's a, it's a campus that's only active on Sundays.

03:14.758 --> 03:19.685
And usually I found it to be most active on Sundays between say noon and about one o'clock.

03:20.926 --> 03:24.011
Our South Campus is, it's all old Kenton Road.

03:25.252 --> 03:26.514
It's out of Marigos.

03:29.474 --> 03:38.643
because I can't tell you how many Sundays I go to a merry-goes for lunch, and I'll walk in and say, I don't know, 15 church people.

03:39.945 --> 03:42.988
So Dana, I don't count that on our worship statistics for the conference.

03:43.028 --> 03:46.211
Don't worry, I'm not counting, I'm not double dipping, I'm not counting it twice.

03:46.572 --> 03:50.956
But I joke all the time about how that's our south campus.

03:51.677 --> 03:56.562
And I say it jokingly, but there is some beauty to that seeing

03:57.218 --> 03:59.340
Church folk outside of church, you know?

04:00.321 --> 04:13.976
Well, one of the things I love seeing is when I see on social media or things like that, seeing church folk that are eating dinner together, or going to a ballgame together, are just living life together.

04:14.456 --> 04:23.346
Doing life together is an overused church phrase that's said far too often, but there is something beautiful

04:23.554 --> 04:34.186
something beautiful about seeing the church community existing beyond just this location, but existing wherever we as the church find ourselves.

04:34.226 --> 04:44.657
And so that goes to the importance of, yes, physical worship is important as the writer to Hebrews says, do not neglect the gathering together or sort of prone to do.

04:45.178 --> 04:46.980
It's important to be physically gathered together.

04:47.821 --> 04:52.626
But I know we have friends watching online right now who would love to physically be here, but cannot.

04:54.210 --> 04:59.915
And I praise God that there are opportunities for individuals to remain connected to our church even when they can't physically be here.

05:01.317 --> 05:07.923
There's something good about the church and all the places that exist and all the places that God grants us to be together.

05:08.063 --> 05:13.468
Whether that be here in our sanctuary, whether that be in America, whether that be in a ballgame, whether that be wherever.

05:14.809 --> 05:15.350
That's beautiful.

05:16.651 --> 05:22.577
We are wrapping up a little series today that talks about how it is that we know God.

05:22.597 --> 05:24.018
And we've talked about these things.

05:25.154 --> 05:30.943
Genesis, sorry, I will, you know, Kelly read, Kelly read today about being salt and light from the scripture.

05:31.023 --> 05:33.046
I preached in that passage a few weeks back.

05:33.486 --> 05:34.548
We're called to be salt and light.

05:34.728 --> 05:35.630
We're called to be different.

05:37.252 --> 05:39.275
Jesus prays in John 17, three.

05:40.477 --> 05:43.682
For us to know eternal life, and that's knowing the Father and the Son who He has sinned.

05:43.902 --> 05:46.966
So our ultimate faith is grounded in knowing Jesus.

05:47.507 --> 05:48.509
Well, how do we know Jesus?

05:48.949 --> 05:54.738
I believe the three best ways we can experience Jesus fully are through reading our Bible, praying, and then going to church.

05:55.458 --> 06:05.732
And now, I told you, I got this saying from a spiritual director of mine who would always say, read your Bible, pray, and stay in love with God's people.

06:06.212 --> 06:08.716
Well, stay in love with God's people doesn't fit good in a bumper sticker.

06:08.936 --> 06:09.897
So I kind of changed that.

06:10.899 --> 06:13.041
So I kind of shortened it to go to church.

06:13.061 --> 06:17.668
But go to church isn't a perfect phrase either.

06:18.649 --> 06:25.458
Because going to church implies that the totality of our faith is found in this location.

06:26.466 --> 06:30.352
So when I say go to church, that's not really, that's not really the right phrase either.

06:31.333 --> 06:34.879
Really, I mean be the church.

06:37.142 --> 06:37.723
Be the church.

06:39.185 --> 06:43.632
When we are the church, something beautiful happens.

06:44.273 --> 06:48.359
And friends, the church is imperfect.

06:48.880 --> 06:49.721
Don't know if you know that or not.

06:50.402 --> 06:52.305
It doesn't happen here, but some people gossip in church.

06:52.425 --> 06:53.246
I know we don't do that here.

06:54.348 --> 06:55.730
Some churches have dissension.

06:55.970 --> 06:56.531
in fighting.

06:57.271 --> 06:58.873
Some churches have all manner of things.

07:00.094 --> 07:07.902
The church will never be a perfect entity the side of glory because the church is made up of imperfect people.

07:09.904 --> 07:11.585
The church is made up of imperfect people.

07:12.806 --> 07:21.054
And so if we're expecting to find perfection in the church, the only perfection you're ever going to find in the church is the perfection of Jesus Christ.

07:22.636 --> 07:24.818
You'll never find the perfection of people.

07:25.570 --> 07:27.674
You'll only find the perfection of Jesus Christ.

07:27.694 --> 07:34.305
I want to read to you a quote from Screwtape Letters, if I saved it in here and I hope I hadn't deleted it already.

07:34.826 --> 07:43.101
I want to get this, you know, I like to wing my serious Lewis quotes, but sometimes I wanted to write this one down because it was so good.

07:45.405 --> 07:50.514
But Lewis says, if you don't know Screwtape Letters,

07:52.098 --> 07:57.443
It's a book that Lewis wrote where it's one senior devil in hell trying to keep a junior devil from growing.

07:58.224 --> 08:08.214
And in this, in this, this letter, he writes to the younger devil named, named Wyrmwood.

08:08.735 --> 08:10.737
You know, next group tapes the younger devil, Wyrmwood's the uncle.

08:10.997 --> 08:19.506
Wyrmwood writes, he says, never let them see the enemy in his body as we see it.

08:20.386 --> 08:27.094
He says, do not let them see it with banners unfurled victorious throughout the ages.

08:29.037 --> 08:32.481
Use his neighbors as our allies.

08:33.642 --> 08:38.148
If he sees the body as the churches, we see it that he will be enthralled by it.

08:38.989 --> 08:47.279
But if so happens, the person on his pew happens to have squeaky shoes or bad breath.

08:48.140 --> 08:49.522
When he's handed a liturgy,

08:50.082 --> 08:52.426
that neither the greeter nor himself understands.

08:53.888 --> 09:06.469
When he sees the church made up of people that are naive and imperfect, we will use that against the enemy to say that the faith can't possibly be true.

09:07.931 --> 09:08.993
I love clearly says this.

09:09.053 --> 09:13.500
He says, never let him, the Christian, see the churches, we see it.

09:13.901 --> 09:17.106
The devil does not see the church in its imperfections.

09:17.954 --> 09:25.762
The devil sees the church as the undefeated, glorious body of Christ that has withstood the testing of hellfire throughout centuries.

09:27.784 --> 09:32.448
We see the church as the imperfect people who sit beside us.

09:34.150 --> 09:36.092
We see the church in its imperfections.

09:36.973 --> 09:38.214
The devil sees it for what it is.

09:39.155 --> 09:43.119
We see it in its fallen nature because we are all fallen.

09:43.139 --> 09:46.162
So if we can, if the devil can get us to see the church,

09:47.330 --> 09:56.020
as nothing more than imperfect people who hurt our feelings sometimes, then he's got us where he wants us.

09:57.121 --> 09:57.662
I love that.

09:58.363 --> 10:00.465
I love that because we can forget.

10:00.505 --> 10:07.012
We can forget how glorious and how beautiful the church is because of so many things.

10:09.135 --> 10:13.300
So I wanted to tell you a little story about church.

10:13.980 --> 10:15.442
Not a story, just something I believe.

10:16.770 --> 10:22.899
And I think something that resonates for us here at St. Matthew's and stuff that I've been playing around with.

10:22.919 --> 10:31.712
Those that come to my Wednesday night, Bible studies know that my Wednesday night, Bible studies sometimes is my lab where I experiment with things and I kind of see a certain concepts work.

10:31.733 --> 10:34.036
And if y'all look at me like I'm crazy, I think, well, I did work.

10:34.096 --> 10:34.837
So let's not go there.

10:36.780 --> 10:43.190
So I wanted to tell you a story about a pastor that some of you may know and remember and love.

10:44.151 --> 10:46.034
You want to hear from our pastors, Bill Macholily.

10:46.658 --> 10:51.786
Bill was the pastor here at St. Matthew's, of what, 2000 or so, I think, roughly.

10:52.207 --> 10:53.148
From there he went to Tupelo.

10:53.589 --> 11:00.339
And Bill remains and is a respected leader, both in the United Methodist Church, but in our annual conference.

11:00.379 --> 11:01.621
He's a retired bishop now.

11:02.583 --> 11:14.962
And in 2004, Bill was at the floor of General Conference, the great gathering of United Methodist from all over the world, when the church was in one of its many fights.

11:16.258 --> 11:40.242
And Bill gave a speech that's always resonated with me where he talked about this great, moderate, Methodist middle that is not swung by either extremes, but is this great, great middle of individuals who may or may not always agree with each other.

11:40.578 --> 11:46.944
but who want to live with each other and serve with each other and love each other and be the church together.

11:47.084 --> 11:50.087
And I've always thought that was a beautiful concept.

11:50.588 --> 11:54.592
And I've always thought that's one of the things that I want to base my ministry around is this great.

11:55.072 --> 11:59.997
I believe fully that there's more that unites us than divides us.

12:01.439 --> 12:01.879
I believe that.

12:03.481 --> 12:05.423
I'm a moderate is what I call myself.

12:06.544 --> 12:08.946
I'm a moderate and I want to speak to that.

12:09.282 --> 12:12.466
Because we hear the word moderate and we think wishy-washy.

12:13.587 --> 12:14.608
You know, do we think right?

12:15.349 --> 12:15.970
We think wishy-washy.

12:15.990 --> 12:17.632
Oh, those martyrs that can't make up their minds.

12:20.135 --> 12:23.579
A moderate is not someone without strong beliefs.

12:25.721 --> 12:36.434
Moderates have, many of us, myself included, have strong beliefs on issues of theology, have strong beliefs on issues of politics.

12:37.378 --> 12:51.635
I don't have very strong beliefs on various things, but what makes a moderate, a moderate is the fact that we will not sacrifice relationships for those beliefs.

12:54.239 --> 13:06.834
I have strong beliefs about many things, strong beliefs about a whole bunch of stuff, but I love you more than I love my particularities of theology or politics.

13:08.642 --> 13:15.970
And I will not allow my particular use of theology or politics to divide me from you.

13:17.672 --> 13:24.840
Because if I am only surrounded by those who agree with me on everything, then what good is that?

13:25.120 --> 13:25.941
I'll never grow.

13:26.282 --> 13:27.102
I'll never learn.

13:27.383 --> 13:28.524
I'll never be made holy.

13:30.486 --> 13:33.970
I think the path of Jesus

13:34.114 --> 13:39.720
calls us to a path of discipleship, but a path of reconciliation with all people.

13:42.042 --> 13:45.225
There are not many places in our world, friends.

13:45.906 --> 14:02.482
There are not many places left in the United States of America and left in the church in America, where individuals can have differences of theological or political opinions and still say, I love you more than that.

14:03.618 --> 14:08.203
and still say, I will stand by you, even if we disagree.

14:08.483 --> 14:10.986
And by the way, you know who is the forefather of that movement?

14:12.248 --> 14:12.888
John Wesley.

14:14.050 --> 14:21.998
Wesley said, on the essentials unity, on the non-essentials diversity, but in all things charity.

14:25.322 --> 14:28.946
I believe friends that our world

14:29.058 --> 14:30.560
is in need of this.

14:30.841 --> 14:32.183
I think we are tired.

14:32.323 --> 14:37.652
I think we are so tired of the polarization and the division that is infected our world.

14:38.934 --> 14:49.272
I think we're tired of the polarization and ideology that sometimes infects the church because friends, the church can be about nothing more than Jesus Christ.

14:50.754 --> 14:53.138
The church cannot be about politics.

14:53.762 --> 14:55.965
The church cannot be about ideology.

14:56.125 --> 15:00.271
There's a million places outside this place that could talk about politics.

15:00.292 --> 15:03.696
There's a million places outside this church that could talk about what divides us.

15:04.097 --> 15:07.622
There are a million places where we can make our stand and say, here's what I'm going to do.

15:07.782 --> 15:12.509
But friends, the only thing I will stand on is the cross of Christ.

15:14.612 --> 15:21.202
And I will not allow temporal earthly things that will cease

15:22.434 --> 15:24.716
to be the foundation of the church.

15:24.997 --> 15:26.398
The church is one foundation.

15:26.699 --> 15:28.360
Is Jesus Christ her king?

15:36.049 --> 15:37.410
I challenge you to be that church.

15:41.034 --> 15:44.598
I challenge you to be that church built on Christ alone.

15:47.040 --> 15:52.306
My desire, my dream for St. Matthews, I believe there are hundreds

15:52.514 --> 15:56.542
maybe thousands of people in the metro area looking for this.

15:58.485 --> 16:01.371
Looking for a place to put aside these divisions.

16:02.673 --> 16:06.400
As important as they may be, because remember, I'm not saying you can't have opinions.

16:06.621 --> 16:07.322
Let me be clear.

16:08.083 --> 16:12.392
I'm not saying you can't believe important things about doctrine or even politics.

16:12.532 --> 16:13.714
I'm not saying that.

16:15.362 --> 16:19.709
But I'm saying they cannot be the foundation of our life.

16:20.009 --> 16:22.593
It can only be Jesus Christ.

16:24.196 --> 16:35.794
I still have hope for what Bill called that great Methodist moderate's middle because I think that is the path upon which Christ calls us to be.

16:37.058 --> 16:38.741
That is the path that our world needs.

16:38.961 --> 16:51.119
And that is the only way that's going to heal our nation, heal our world and heal our hopes is that if we say, yes, we can believe what we believe and I'm not discouraging anyone from believing their opinions or their thoughts.

16:52.261 --> 16:56.267
This is, I am not calling for uniformity.

16:58.831 --> 17:00.033
I'm calling for unity.

17:02.517 --> 17:03.378
There's a difference.

17:06.914 --> 17:13.402
No one should be cast aside for their politics or their doctrine.

17:17.687 --> 17:18.849
We need less of that, though.

17:20.851 --> 17:22.092
We need a whole lot more Jesus.

17:25.577 --> 17:33.266
And to go from preaching to Madeleine, we need each other because we make each other holy.

17:35.202 --> 17:36.804
Relationships are a means of grace.

17:37.664 --> 17:40.767
You know, I mentioned John 17, three, John 17 earlier.

17:41.588 --> 17:43.010
I talked about this last week in intersection.

17:43.070 --> 17:44.691
That's Jesus high priestly prayer.

17:45.832 --> 17:46.914
And then Jesus high priestly prayer.

17:46.934 --> 17:48.535
He's praying for the apostles of that day.

17:48.595 --> 17:49.776
He's praying for us as well.

17:51.298 --> 17:53.020
And twice in that prayer, he prays for unity.

17:53.620 --> 17:53.900
Twice.

17:54.701 --> 17:54.981
Twice.

17:55.422 --> 17:57.043
He prays for the unity of the apostles.

17:57.624 --> 17:59.626
They praise for the unity of the church that is to come.

18:01.468 --> 18:03.730
For twice in this last prayer, he prays for that.

18:05.474 --> 18:08.658
Why is it unity sometimes the first thing we throw out?

18:10.500 --> 18:11.922
It seemed to matter a lot to Jesus.

18:12.082 --> 18:20.994
It shouldn't matter to us because our unity makes us stronger because those folk who are different than us, it's hard to love them sometimes.

18:22.696 --> 18:24.157
But that's the test of our faith, friends.

18:26.060 --> 18:30.205
Doris Daly, this Catholic social reformer, said once.

18:31.827 --> 18:34.130
She said, you only love God.

18:34.978 --> 18:37.261
as much as you love the person, you love the least.

18:40.124 --> 18:44.770
James said, how can you say you love God who is unseen, yet you hate your neighbor who is seen?

18:46.613 --> 18:47.754
I've heard someone else feel like this.

18:49.016 --> 18:53.141
How will people believe a God they can't see loves them?

18:55.063 --> 18:57.907
When a church they can see doesn't seem to like them.

19:00.550 --> 19:03.794
The test of our faith is not loving the folks who agree with this, that's easy.

19:05.762 --> 19:07.204
Love the folk who disagree with us.

19:10.788 --> 19:16.976
So if you're a woke liberal, the test of your faith is, can you love the MAGA Republican?

19:20.541 --> 19:25.627
And if you're a MAGA Republican, the test of your faith is, can you love a woke liberal?

19:28.010 --> 19:30.473
And if we build our house on the world, we can't.

19:31.415 --> 19:32.896
Not only can we, can we not?

19:33.077 --> 19:34.098
We're told we shouldn't.

19:36.002 --> 19:39.827
Because they are the problem, whoever they are.

19:39.887 --> 19:49.140
The friends, if we build our house on Jesus Christ, not only can we love them, we must love them.

19:49.180 --> 20:00.576
Because Jesus says there are two types of folk in the world, our friends and our enemies, and we're called to love both of them.

20:00.596 --> 20:04.882
I believe there are hundreds of people in the metro area.

20:05.282 --> 20:08.667
who are dying for the freedom that comes from this type of thing.

20:11.210 --> 20:12.872
So my challenge to you is the church.

20:13.413 --> 20:14.595
My challenge to you is your pastor.

20:16.357 --> 20:17.318
It's for us to live into this.

20:19.461 --> 20:24.668
My dream for St. Matthew uses for everyone of this type of belief system to find theirself to our church.

20:27.452 --> 20:30.596
There's a lot of folk out there that need who we are.

20:33.400 --> 20:34.962
So my challenge for you is to go find them.

20:35.458 --> 20:35.858
Me too.

20:38.161 --> 20:42.486
And let's build this kingdom that God's building here for his glory.

20:44.429 --> 20:45.310
We're called to be the church.

20:46.992 --> 20:48.553
So we're called to be part of this community.

20:49.575 --> 20:53.539
The way I put it is recalled to worship weekly.

20:56.102 --> 20:58.385
Weekly worship, weekly small group daily service.

20:58.445 --> 21:02.770
That's what I think it means to be part of the community is to value weekly worship.

21:03.650 --> 21:07.616
I've joked with you before, you start reading the Bible through, you hit Leviticus and you tap out.

21:09.418 --> 21:19.252
Leviticus is a book that might seem hard for us at our modern age, but you know what, Leviticus keeps hitting over and over and over and over again?

21:20.314 --> 21:20.654
Worship.

21:21.656 --> 21:24.219
When you sacrifice do this, on this day do this.

21:24.440 --> 21:25.301
When you do this, do this.

21:25.682 --> 21:27.644
Leviticus is an entire book about worship.

21:27.865 --> 21:31.570
Now, it's a little bit different from how we worship, but it's a book about worship.

21:33.090 --> 21:41.167
Worship matters to us, as the writer at the Hebrew says, don't neglect the gathering together of the brethren, like worship.

21:41.187 --> 21:41.668
This matters.

21:42.310 --> 21:45.075
Whether you're here in person or online, this matters.

21:46.258 --> 21:47.120
Weekly worship.

21:47.140 --> 21:47.962
Weekly small group.

21:48.402 --> 21:49.685
Because here's the good thing about worship.

21:49.705 --> 21:53.874
Worship is great, but you know where life change happens in small groups.

21:54.306 --> 21:55.808
And that's Wesleyan.

21:56.149 --> 22:00.195
Wesley was all about class meetings and societies and bands.

22:00.515 --> 22:06.304
Wesley called the Methodist of his day and of our day to be connected to each other through small groups.

22:06.484 --> 22:08.507
Because it's the small groups you get in each other's business.

22:09.128 --> 22:11.011
It's small groups where you go deep in Scripture.

22:11.232 --> 22:13.335
It's small groups where you hold each other accountable.

22:13.575 --> 22:15.538
It's small groups where you live together.

22:15.938 --> 22:17.781
Now that small group could be a Sunday school.

22:18.001 --> 22:18.982
It could be a Bible study.

22:19.162 --> 22:21.025
It could be a service group like the choir.

22:21.045 --> 22:25.371
It could be anything, but we can't do this Christianity thing alone.

22:26.433 --> 22:27.895
So we're called to worship weekly.

22:28.776 --> 22:32.721
We're called to be in small group weekly and we're called to serve daily.

22:34.744 --> 22:37.528
As the great quote says, Christ has no hands, but yours.

22:37.568 --> 22:38.970
He has no feet, but yours.

22:40.833 --> 22:44.658
How will the world know we love them unless we love them?

22:46.370 --> 22:57.624
How the world know there's a Savior who loves them, unless we take that good news of Christ to them.

22:57.644 --> 23:00.828
We have a mission, y'all.

23:00.848 --> 23:04.172
I think we have something special here that is not found in many places.

23:05.394 --> 23:08.498
I think we don't, we struggle with what that means, but we know it, don't we?

23:10.220 --> 23:15.026
But I think the fact that we are seeking to build a kingdom here, the phrase that you used in

23:15.650 --> 23:27.647
church stuff is a purple church, to church with some Republicans and some Democrats, to church with some liberals and some conservatives, to church with all manner of opinions.

23:27.707 --> 23:31.091
And so they call it a purple church, but you know what I've always called that church?

23:32.854 --> 23:36.499
The United Methodist Church, because that's who we are.

23:38.261 --> 23:42.067
That's who we are, because it's about Jesus.

23:43.649 --> 23:44.530
It's about Jesus.

23:45.474 --> 23:46.055
Nothing else.

23:48.137 --> 23:52.841
So I'm not calling you to not believe what you believe or not hold fast what you hold fast to.

23:54.563 --> 23:56.405
I'm just saying don't break relationship over it.

23:58.287 --> 23:59.408
And don't find your hope in it.

24:01.470 --> 24:07.856
Because my hope is found in nothing less than Jesus' blood and righteousness.

24:09.097 --> 24:14.162
I dare not trust the sweetest frame, but holy lean on Jesus' name.

24:15.650 --> 24:25.235
own Christ, the solid rock I stand, all other ground is sinking sand, all other ground is sinking sand.

24:27.100 --> 24:29.807
The name of the Father and the Son, the Holy Spirit.

24:30.389 --> 24:30.930
Let us pray.

